<h1 style="color: rgb(102, 0, 0); text-align: center;">Computer and
Network Privacy and Security: Ethical, Legal, and Technical
Considerations</h1>
<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;">
<h3 style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 40px;">You have zero
privacy anyway. Get over it.</h3>
<div style="margin-left: 120px;"><cite>Scott Mcnealy, CEO Sun
Microsystems, January 1999</cite></div>
<cite><a href="http://www.schneier.com/crypto-gram-0707.html"></a></cite>
<h3 style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 40px;">History will record
what we, here in the early decades of the information age, did to
foster freedom, liberty, and democracy. Did we build information
technologies that protected people&#8217;s freedoms even during times when
society tried to subvert them? Or did we build technologies that could
easily be modified to watch and control?</h3>
<cite></cite>
<div style="margin-left: 120px;"><cite>Bruce Schneier, Risks of Data
Reuse, <a href="http://www.schneier.com/crypto-gram-0707.html">CRYPTO-GRAM,
July 15, 2007</a></cite><cite></cite></div>
<br>
